    "body": "Hi all, I am trying to install a version of skopeo with the `list-tags` flag available. Is there any repository where I can pull a skopeo with newer versions? This is the version I currently have installed:\n```bash\\n Package                                                               Arch                                                                  Version                                                                           Repository                                                                                Size\\nInstalling:\n skopeo                                                                x86_64                                                                1:0.1.40-12.el7_9                                                                 rhel-7-server-extras-rpms                                                                5.8 M\n\nTransaction Summary\\n```",
    "comments": [
        {
            "user": "mtrmac",
            "body": "Thanks for your report.\n\nFor Red Hat officially-supported versions included in/around RHEL, if any, please contact official Red Hat support through access.redhat.com\n\nAs for unsupported upstream or third-party builds, I’m not sure. @lsm5 , do you know? The Kubic libcontainers repo seems to have RHEL 7 disabled, by now at least."
        },
        {
            "user": "lsm5",
            "body": "@pkddacoliat hi, rhel7 isn't going to get any official package updates anymore. Also, the Kubic packages were disabled for CentOS7 and other older distros because of really outdated dependencies. See: https://podman.io/blogs/2021/03/02/podman-support-for-older-distros.html . I don't know if there are any third parties building newer skopeo for el7.\n\nSo, you could either install from source, or switch to a newer rhel/centos. Sorry about the inconvenience. \n\nClosing this.."
        }
